<text top="326" left="502" width="287" height="13" font="1">FIR  filters  are  most  widely  used  in  FPGA </text>
<text top="344" left="460" width="329" height="13" font="1">implementations  because  they  have  linear  phase. </text>
<text top="361" left="460" width="329" height="13" font="1">Compared  to  IIR  filters,  FIR  filters  have  simple  and </text>
<text top="378" left="460" width="329" height="13" font="1">regular  structures  which  are  easy  to  implement  on </text>
<text top="395" left="460" width="329" height="13" font="1">hardware. However FIR filters require higher number </text>
<text top="413" left="460" width="329" height="13" font="1">of  taps  compared  to  IIR  filters  to  achieve  the  same </text>
<text top="430" left="460" width="154" height="13" font="1">frequency specifications. </text>
